the early 80s have a weird timeline for computers

the IBM PC is 1981: 16bit at ~5mhz, maxing out at 640k, lot of CPU but no graphical power or sound, expensive
c64 is 1982: AFTER the PC, but 8bit, 1mhz, cheap, great graphics and sound for the time

both use text-based interfaces
